MIDDLE LAKE AT LAUDERDALE WI - TOP
LAKE HIGH AND NO WAKE AFTER SIGNIFICANT RAIN FALL
LAKE LEVEL HIGH AFTER SIGNIFICANT RAIN FALL. TESTED AFTER 2 WEEKS OF NO WAKE
Not as windy as the other lakes. It was easier to see the disc which is probably why the reading is a little deeper. Temperature was 66F- sunny and moderate wind.
Light wind- calm water with some chop due to boats.
sunny- calm- light wind- definite algae bloom
Definite algae bloom. Lake was very busy all week- so the water has been choppy every day. The daytime temperature was in the upper 80's with a gentle breeze.
Had problems with the HACH meter. The screen fogged up and we couldn't read the temperatures. I was able to correct the problem by warming the meter and drying it out.

Lost of boat traffic. A wake boat nearly launched me out of my 16' Alumacraft. Sunny with scattered clouds. Lots of chop and chunks of weeds floating in the area of testing. I noticed two large chunks of bog floating in the lake - one on each side of Middle Lake approxinately 1/2 way between the Landing and the channels to Mill/Green Lakes.
Sunny. No Wind. Light boat traffic.
